tps://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]},"_embedded":{"author":[{"id":1,"name":"scottsweb","url":"","description":"","link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/author/scottsweb/","slug":"scottsweb","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/users"}]}}],"wp:term":[[{"id":5,"link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/category/design/","name":"Design","slug":"design","taxonomy":"category","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/categories/5"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/categories"}],"about":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/taxonomies/category"}],"wp:post_type":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/posts?categories=5"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}],[]]}},{"id":1179,"date":"2014-02-05T10:25:12","date_gmt":"2014-02-05T10:25:12","guid":{"rendered":"http://scott.ee/?p=1179"},"modified":"2017-12-16T19:52:47","modified_gmt":"2017-12-16T19:52:47","slug":"wp-instagram-widget","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/wp-instagram-widget/","title":{"rendered":"WP Instagram Widget"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"intro\">A few weeks ago and without much noise I pushed the unimaginatively named WP Instagram widget to <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-instagram-widget/\">WordPress.org</a>. The widget is a no fuss WordPress widget to showcase your latest Instagram pics.</p>\n<p><noscript><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1508\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/scottsweb.mystagingwebsite.com/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?w=900&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Instagram Logo on blue background\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=250%2C140&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=768%2C429&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=700%2C391&amp;ssl=1 700w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=120%2C67&amp;ssl=1 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"></noscript><div class=\"lazy\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1508\" src=\"\" alt=\"Instagram Logo on blue background\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-src=\"https://i2.wp.com/scottsweb.mystagingwebsite.com/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?w=900&amp;ssl=1\" data-srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=250%2C140&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=768%2C429&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=700%2C391&amp;ssl=1 700w, https://i0.wp.com/api.scott.ee/wp-content/uploads/journal-wp-instagram-widget.jpg?resize=120%2C67&amp;ssl=1 120w\"></div></p>\n<p>The plugin was written for some client work @ <a title=\"VIP WordPress agency\" href=\"http://codeforthepeople.com\">CFTP</a> and is unique in that it requires no authentication against the Instagram API. Instead it scrapes the publicly accessible JSON from the Instagram website.</p>\n<p>There is a increasing trend within the world of startups to lock your content away. Twitter taking away RSS is a good example of this and it&rsquo;s not something I agree with. Of course authentication should be required for certain features but making it harder to access my own content is not cool.</p>\n<p>In a short time the plugin has proved rather popular so it looks like folk are quite fond of this simple approach too. The popularity is such that I am considering using the same approach in a few more plugins.</p>\n<p>The widget has two filters. The first allows you adjust that cache time for retrieving the images from Instagram:</p>\n<pre><code data-language=\"php\">add_filter('null_instagram_cache_time', 'my_cache_time');\r\nfunction my_cache_time() {\r\n    return HOUR_IN_SECONDS;\r\n}</code></pre>\n<p>The second allows you to filter video results from the widget:</p>\n<pre><code data-language=\"php\">add_filter('wpiw_images_only', '__return_true');</code></pre>\n<p>In version 1.3 I have also added two new hooks for adding custom output before and after the widget:</p>\n<pre><code>wpiw_before_widget\r\nwpiw_after_widget\r\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can contribute to the plugin on <a href=\"https://github.com/cftp/wp-instagram-widget\">GitHub</a> or:</p>\n<p><a class=\"abutton btn btn--primary\" title=\"Download WP Instagram Widget from WordPress.org\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-instagram-widget/\">Download from WordPress.org</a></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"WP Instagram Widget is a simple plugin for WordPress that makes it easy to showcase your latest Instagram photos and videos on your website.","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[11],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/1179"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/comments?post=1179"}],"version-history":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/1179/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/media?parent=1179"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/categories?post=1179"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/tags?post=1179"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]},"_embedded":{"author":[{"id":1,"name":"scottsweb","url":"","description":"","link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/author/scottsweb/","slug":"scottsweb","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/users"}]}}],"wp:term":[[{"id":11,"link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/category/wordpress/","name":"WordPress","slug":"wordpress","taxonomy":"category","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/categories/11"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/categories"}],"about":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/taxonomies/category"}],"wp:post_type":[{"href":"https://api.scott.ee/wp-json/wp/v2/posts?categories=11"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}],[]]}},{"id":1027,"date":"2013-11-06T21:47:18","date_gmt":"2013-11-06T21:47:18","guid":{"rendered":"http://scott.cloudcontrol.me/?p=1027"},"modified":"2017-12-16T17:42:32","modified_gmt":"2017-12-16T17:42:32","slug":"bomb-garden","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://api.scott.ee/journal/bomb-garden/","title":{"rendered":"The Bomb In The Garden"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<blockquote><p>It&rsquo;s now or nev&shy;er for the web. The web is a medi&shy;um for cre&shy;ators, in&shy;clud&shy;ing de&shy;sign&shy;ers. But af&shy;ter 20 years, the web still has no cul&shy;ture of de&shy;sign ex&shy;cel&shy;lence. Why is that?</p></blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"http://unitscale.com/mb/bomb-in-the-garden/\">unitscale.com</a>.</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"It&rsquo;s now or nev&shy;er for the web. The web is a medi&shy;um for cre&shy;ators, in&shy;c